<subSubSection pageId="84" pageNumber="85" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1437,289,746]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,289,314]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Remarks.</emphasis>
This genus was established by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mistshenko" box="[633,921,289,314]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Mistshenko, L. L. (1951 b) Revision of Orthoptera of the genus Tropidauchen Sauss. (Saltatoria - Orthoptera, Acrididae) and related genera. Dokladij Akademii Nauk SSSR 57, 737 - 740 [Russian]" type="journal article" year="1951" yearSuffix="b">Mistshenko (1951b: 738)</bibRefCitation>
by the shape of frontal ridge, the vertex and hind femur. Dirsh (1952: 95, 97) explaining in detail synonymized it with 
<taxonomicName box="[1044,1199,325,350]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Tropidauchen" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1044,1199,325,350]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Tropidauchen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<bibRefCitation author="Bey-Bienko" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Bey-Bienko, G. Ya &amp; Mistshenko, L. L. (1951) Fauna of the USSR Locusts and Grasshoppers of the U. S. S. R. and Adjacent Countries. Part 1. Zoological Institute of the USSR Academy of Sciences, 38, 1 - 400." type="journal article" year="1951">Bey-Bienko &amp; Mistshenko (1951: 332)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mirzayans" box="[450,705,361,386]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Mirzayans, H. (1959) Liste des Orthopteres et leurs distribution en Iran. Entomologie et Phytopathologie Appliquees, 18, 10 - 30." type="journal article" year="1959">Mirzayans (1959: 15)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Shumakov" box="[723,980,361,386]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Shumakov, E. M. (1963) Acridoidea of Afghanistan and Iran. Horae Societatis Entomologicae Unionis Soveticae, 49, 3 - 248 [Russian]" type="journal article" year="1963">Shumakov (1963: 47)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bey-Bienko" box="[997,1284,361,386]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Bey-Bienko, G. Ya. (1963) Sur les insectes orthopteroides de l' Afghanistan (Contribution a l' etude de la faune de l' Afghanistan, 69). Horae Societatis Entomologicae Unionis Soveticae, 49, 249 - 284. [Russian]" type="journal article" year="1963">Bey-Bienko (1963: 268)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bey-Bienko" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Bey-Bienko, G. Ya. (1967) Some orthopteroid insects of the orders Blattoptera, Orthoptera and Dermaptera from Afghanistan. Acta entomologica bohemslovaca, 64, 407 - 438. [Russian, English abstract]" type="journal article" year="1967">Bey-Bienko (1967: 427)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Descamps" box="[298,542,397,422]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Descamps, M. (1967) Revue et diagnose preliminaire de quelques Pamphagidae et Acrididae d' Iran (Orth. Acridoidea). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 72, 27 - 37." type="journal article" year="1967">Descamps (1967: 28)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cejchan" box="[554,789,397,422]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Cejchan, A. (1969) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Fauna Afghanistans. Acridoidea, Orth. Casopis Moravskeho Musea, Vedy prirodni, 54, 229 - 276." type="journal article" year="1969">Cejchan (1969: 233)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Presa" box="[801,1103,397,422]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Presa J. J. &amp; Garcia M. D. (1983) Inventario preliminar de los Pamphagidae (Orthoptera) de la region paleartica. Anales de la Universidad de Murcia, 42, 3 - 42." type="journal article" year="1983">Presa &amp; Garcia (1983: 29)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Otte" box="[1115,1303,398,422]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Otte, D. (1994) Orthoptera Species File 3. Grasshoppers [Acridomorpha] B. Pamphagoidea. Orthopterists' Society &amp; Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 241 pp." type="book" year="1994">Otte (1994: 187)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hodjat" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Hodjat, S. H. (2012) An update list of Pamphagidae Brumster 1840 (Insecta: Orthoptera) of Iran with a key to the genera. Journal of Crop Protection 1 (3), 261 - 270." type="journal article" year="2012">Hodjat (2012: 262, 264, 266)</bibRefCitation>
gave 
<taxonomicName box="[471,582,434,457]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Saxetania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[471,582,434,457]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Saxetania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid genus. Only 
<bibRefCitation author="Mirzayans" box="[855,1057,433,458]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Mirzayans, H. (1998) Insects of Iran. The list of Orthoptera in the insect collection of Plant Pests and Diseases Research Institute of Iran. Pamphagidae and Pyrgomorphidae. Plant Pests and Diseases Reseach Institute, Insect Taxonomy Research Department, Entomological Publications, Tehran, 3, 40 pp." type="book" year="1998">Mirzayans (1998)</bibRefCitation>
listed some species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1325,1435,434,457]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Saxetania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1325,1435,434,457]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Saxetania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName box="[222,377,469,494]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Tropidauchen" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[222,377,469,494]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Tropidauchen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bey-Bienko" box="[391,758,469,494]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Bey-Bienko, G. Ya. &amp; Richter, W. (1960) Acridoidea aus Iran (Orthoptera). Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, 37, 1 - 19." type="journal article" year="1960">Bey-Bienko &amp; Richter (1960: 9)</bibRefCitation>
reported it as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName box="[1082,1237,469,494]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Tropidauchen" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1082,1237,469,494]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Tropidauchen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the first time, but 
<bibRefCitation author="Bey-Bienko" box="[197,410,505,530]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Bey-Bienko, G. Ya. (1963) Sur les insectes orthopteroides de l' Afghanistan (Contribution a l' etude de la faune de l' Afghanistan, 69). Horae Societatis Entomologicae Unionis Soveticae, 49, 249 - 284. [Russian]" type="journal article" year="1963">Bey-Bienko (1963</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bey-Bienko" box="[425,482,505,530]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Bey-Bienko, G. Ya. (1967) Some orthopteroid insects of the orders Blattoptera, Orthoptera and Dermaptera from Afghanistan. Acta entomologica bohemslovaca, 64, 407 - 438. [Russian, English abstract]" type="journal article" year="1967">1967</bibRefCitation>
) gave it as an independent genus again. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hodjat" box="[959,1120,505,530]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refString="Hodjat, S. H. (2012) An update list of Pamphagidae Brumster 1840 (Insecta: Orthoptera) of Iran with a key to the genera. Journal of Crop Protection 1 (3), 261 - 270." type="journal article" year="2012">Hodjat (2012)</bibRefCitation>
compared both genera and considered them valid. It is not always easy to distinguish both genera using the external structures. As given by Dirsh (1952) some species have interstage characters. On the other hand the male genitalia allow to easily distinguish both genera, mainly the structure of apical valves of penis, which is very distinctive, very large and not covered by the sheath of penis in 
<taxonomicName box="[548,658,650,673]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Saxetania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[548,658,650,673]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Saxetania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[676,771,649,674]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1884,1906]" captionTargetBox="[178,1399,199,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[177,1411,193,1875]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 43. Male phallic complex. a phallus lateral, b phallus dorsal, c epiphallus, d phallus posterior view. 32 Prionosthenus gueleni; 33 Ocnerosthenus brunnerianus; 34 Ocneropsis bethlehemita; 35 Orchamus yersini yersini; 36 Orchamus massai; 37 Paracinipe zebrata; 38 Tropidauchen escalerai; 39 Saxetania (s. str.) cultricolle cultricolle; 40 Saxetania (Cryptonothrotes) pseudoaptera; 41 Saxetania (Mistshenkoella) gorochovi; 42 Paranocarodes straubei; 43 Paranocarodes fieberi. Scales 1 mm (short scale for a, b, c; long scale for d)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208264/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Figs. 39</figureCitation>
a–41a) (small, thin and covered by the sheath of penis in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,306,685,710]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Tropidauchen" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,306,685,710]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Tropidauchen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation box="[329,412,685,710]" captionStart="FIGURES 32 – 43" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1884,1906]" captionTargetBox="[178,1399,199,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[177,1411,193,1875]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 32 – 43. Male phallic complex. a phallus lateral, b phallus dorsal, c epiphallus, d phallus posterior view. 32 Prionosthenus gueleni; 33 Ocnerosthenus brunnerianus; 34 Ocneropsis bethlehemita; 35 Orchamus yersini yersini; 36 Orchamus massai; 37 Paracinipe zebrata; 38 Tropidauchen escalerai; 39 Saxetania (s. str.) cultricolle cultricolle; 40 Saxetania (Cryptonothrotes) pseudoaptera; 41 Saxetania (Mistshenkoella) gorochovi; 42 Paranocarodes straubei; 43 Paranocarodes fieberi. Scales 1 mm (short scale for a, b, c; long scale for d)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/208264/files/figure.png" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
a). The male genitalia of all known species and subspecies of both genera should be checked to determine the correct genus.
</paragraph>
